International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. Key Developments

International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. and ZoomEssence Inc. Mutually Agree to Settle All Claims and Counterclaims Brought in Lawsuit in the United States District Court for District of New Jersey
Jun 23 17
International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. and ZoomEssence Inc. have mutually agreed to settle all claims and counterclaims brought in a lawsuit in the United States District Court for the District of New Jersey. The parties agreed to dismiss their claims against one another, with prejudice and without any admission of liability or wrongful conduct, to avoid any further expense and disruption from the litigation. Under the settlement agreement, IFF will make a one-time payment to ZoomEssence of $56 million and the parties will exchange full mutual releases.


International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. Presents at Deutsche Bank Global Consumer Conference, Jun-13-2017 02:45 PM
May 10 17
International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. Presents at Deutsche Bank Global Consumer Conference, Jun-13-2017 02:45 PM. Venue: InterContinental Paris Le Grand, Paris, France. Speakers: Andreas Fibig, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer.


International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Financial Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Year 2017
May 8 17
International Flavors & Fragrances Inc. reported unaudited consolidated financial results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. Net sales were $828.293 million against $783.312 million a year ago. Operating profit was $134.437 million against $169.933 million a year ago. Income before taxes was $138.487 million against $154.896 million a year ago. Net income was $115.764 million or $1.45 per diluted share against $118.603 million or $1.47 per diluted share a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $21.701 million against $39.943 million a year ago. Additions to property, plant and equipment was $26.662 million against $22.512 million a year ago. Adjusted operating profit (non-GAAP) was $163.510 million against $167.180 million a year ago. Adjusted income before taxes (non-GAAP) was $152.345 million against $152.143 million a year ago. Adjusted net income (non-GAAP) was $121.115 million or $1.52 per diluted share against $116.371 million or $1.45 per diluted share a year ago.

The company provided earnings guidance for 2017. For the period, the company expects sales of 7.5%-8.5%, operating profit of 5.5%-6.5% and EPS of 6.5%-7.5%; and expects adjusted sales of 6.0%-7.0%, adjusted operating profit of 3.0%-4.0% and adjusted EPS of 3.5%-4.5%.


