        Latest Industry News
    


Elon Musk details Tesla Model 3 pricing, range
              
              Tesla Inc.'s  Model 3 will cost $35,000 for a base version and $44,000 for a model with longer range, Chief Executive Elon Musk announced Friday night at an event outside the company's Fremont, Calif., factory. Tesla has announced hundreds of thousands of reservations for the car, which included $1,000 deposits, but only announced the final pricing schedule at the event, where the first 30 Model 3 units were supposed to be delivered to owners. The two options for range introduced Friday night were a Standard edition expected to travel 220 miles on a full charge, and a Long-Range model that would travel 310 miles. Musk reiterated at the event that he expects to soon build the cars at a rate of 5,000 a week, ramping up to 10,000 a week by the end of next year, and that customers who order the cars now would likely receive them late next year.              
              
            

12:33 a.m.  Today12:33 a.m. July 29, 2017








