Fragrance IngredientsOnline Compendium













                        For over 128 years, we have pioneered innovative, high-quality and cost-effective fragrance ingredients
                      

used by perfumers worldwide to create winning fragrances.













 



                                  Starfleur™ 40
                                


                                    A fresh, highly performing floral green, muguet, freesia, aldehydic note with a natural green effect.
                                  



 







What if we could start a revolution in sensorial science?
In search for molecules in the Muguet family, many ingredients were synthesized. Starfleur™ was chosen to be taken forward based on its performance and odor profile. IFF patented it in 2010. It’s useful for: Fresh green florals, Muguet, Lily and Freesia notes, lemon and mandarin fresh citrus types and watery transparent notes.
Discover how Starfleur™ 40 has a natural impression of spring flowers and gives volume and body to a fragrance



                                          Download PDF
                                          








 



                                  Harmonies
                                


                                    A source of inspiration stimulating innovative ways of creating exciting olfactory combinations 
                                  



 







To fuel your imagination and intrigue your creativity IFF perfumery has developed Harmonies. These fine blends, based on IFF specialty ingredients, reveal creative opportunities for your consideration. 

IFF harmonies are a great aid in discovering how to use IFF specialties. They are created to show various effects that can be achieved, providing both olfactive and performance benefits. Meant as a source of inspiration stimulating innovative ways of creating exciting olfactory combinations using Timbersilk™, Starfleur™ 40, Amber Xtreme™ and Pino Acetaldehyde.

As a fine blend or partial building block for your future creations we encourage you to consider these harmonies and in turn embrace the value of IFF specialty ingredients. 
 



                                          Download PDF
                                          








 



                                  Amber Xtreme™
                                


                                    Xtreme Power. Xtreme Performance.
                                  



 







What if we let our senses guide us?
The discovery of Amber Xtreme™ in 2001 represents a triumph of structure-odor relationship intuition. It was a serendipitous discovery that manipulating Galbanum molecules into an ether moiety could lead to molecules with an amber odor. Pursuing this idea on diverse backbones, our scientists identified a plethora of new molecules. The insights gained from this unique structure-odor research led to the discovery of Amber Xtreme™, a uniquely powerful amber woody molecule. With expertise and perseverance, our chemists and process engineers developed a commercially viable process for Amber Xtreme™. A new star was born.
Discover why the power of Amber Xtreme™ is like nothing else



                                          Download PDF
                                          
















What if we could start a revolution in sensorial science?
In search for molecules in the Muguet family, many ingredients were synthesized. Starfleur™ was chosen to be taken forward based on its performance and odor profile. IFF patented it in 2010. It’s useful for: Fresh green florals, Muguet, Lily and Freesia notes, lemon and mandarin fresh citrus types and watery transparent notes.
Discover how Starfleur™ 40 has a natural impression of spring flowers and gives volume and body to a fragrance



